Unless refused licensure in accordance with KRS 304.9-440, a nonresident person shall receive a nonresident independent, staff, or public adjuster license if:
The person is currently licensed in good standing as an independent, staff, or public adjuster in his, her, or its home state;
The person has submitted the proper request for licensure, and has paid the fees required by KRS 304.4-010;
The person has submitted, in a form or format prescribed by the commissioner, the uniform individual application; and
The person's designated home state issues nonresident independent, staff, or public adjuster licenses to persons of Kentucky on the same basis.
